        "subject": "LU-2641 mgs: fix cleanup of MGSSELF_NAME proc file",
        "message": "LU-2641 mgs: fix cleanup of MGSSELF_NAME proc file\n\nCommit 12bac0d9 (v2.6.33) added a WARN_ON for trying to remove\nnonexistent proc entries.\n\nmgs_new_fsdb only calls lproc_mgs_add_live if the fsname isn't \"_mgs\",\nhowever mgs_free_fsdb calls lproc_mgs_del_live unconditionally.\n\nThis triggers the warning.\n\nWe check the FSDB_MGS_SELF bit which is only set when\nfsname == \"_mgs\", so we know to skip the proc entry removal and avoid\nthe warning.\n\nSigned-off-by: Jeff Mahoney <jeffm@suse.com>\nChange-Id: I769701f437ab3d8f537d4b592c7363cf399dbb7c\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_1"
    }
